Happy 18th, right?

16:34.770 --> 16:37.864
♪ I don't wanna be ♪

16:37.864 --> 16:40.792
♪ We only wanna stay young ♪

16:40.792 --> 16:42.003
- Mike.

16:42.003 --> 16:44.853
Be a babe and take a photo
of me over by the treeline?

16:44.853 --> 16:46.323
- Happy to, V.

16:46.323 --> 16:47.793
Happy to.

16:47.793 --> 16:49.173
- I'm not normally one for nostalgia,

16:49.173 --> 16:52.143
but I kinda wanna remember my
last summer here, you know?

16:52.143 --> 16:54.723
- Whoa, slow down.

16:54.723 --> 16:55.556
Last summer?

16:57.157 --> 16:59.103
- The real world calls.

16:59.103 --> 17:00.603
- What, this place isn't real?

17:02.223 --> 17:03.423
- Only when you're here.

17:04.367 --> 17:06.933
♪ We only wanna be free ♪

17:06.933 --> 17:08.906
- I guess we have to
make tonight count, then.

17:11.506 --> 17:12.589
♪ Shouted down, pushed ♪

17:12.589 --> 17:13.913
♪ And we're getting real bushed ♪

17:13.913 --> 17:16.246
♪ Let it go ♪

17:18.596 --> 17:20.076
- This is stupid.

17:23.163 --> 17:23.996
- You're stupid.

17:27.063 --> 17:28.363
- Are you sure about this?

17:30.933 --> 17:32.913
- Oh my god. Not you too!

17:32.913 --> 17:34.983
- I'm just saying.

17:34.983 --> 17:35.823
- You sound like Shawn.

17:35.823 --> 17:36.783
- Peter-
- Exactly.

17:36.783 --> 17:38.286
No, no, exactly like Shawn.

17:39.633 --> 17:41.853
Why is everyone so over
having a good time?

17:41.853 --> 17:43.743
We don't have many summers left to...

17:43.743 --> 17:45.873
Hey, where are you guys going?

17:45.873 --> 17:48.996
- We forgot to close up the
bunks on the south side.

17:49.947 --> 17:50.780
- So?

17:50.780 --> 17:52.563
- So we don't want your
mom blowing a gasket

17:52.563 --> 17:54.243
when she gets back.

17:54.243 --> 17:57.248
- What's she gonna do? Fire you?

17:57.248 --> 17:58.653
(both laugh)

17:58.653 --> 18:01.023
- We're not all McCalisters, Peter.

18:01.023 --> 18:02.523
- Careful. It's dark out there.

18:02.523 --> 18:04.053
- No worries, sis.

18:04.053 --> 18:05.406
I travel smart!

18:06.733 --> 18:07.983
- Give me that.

18:08.876 --> 18:10.053
Give me that back.

18:10.053 --> 18:11.373
- Hey, listen. Pizza's on the way.

18:11.373 --> 18:13.953
He's gonna honk three times
so you know he's here.

18:13.953 --> 18:15.393
- Great. Fine.

18:15.393 --> 18:16.413
You're just gonna miss-

18:16.413 --> 18:17.973
- Oh my god.

18:17.973 --> 18:20.333
His stupid ass...

18:23.313 --> 18:24.906
Agatha. Happy?

18:25.863 --> 18:26.696
- Pacified.

18:26.696 --> 18:28.323
- Yo, Ash.

18:28.323 --> 18:29.223
- Whoa, bitch.

18:29.223 --> 18:33.306
- Man. That skit today stirred my soul.

18:34.173 --> 18:35.346
- That's great, Dylan.

18:36.453 --> 18:38.313
- How's that make you feel?

18:38.313 --> 18:40.476
Your art stirred my soul.

18:42.363 --> 18:44.813
- Well, Ben wrote it, so...

18:47.139 --> 18:48.360
(Ash laughs)

18:48.360 --> 18:49.783
- Faggot.

18:49.783 --> 18:51.476
- Ew. He's disgusting.

18:51.476 --> 18:53.312
- Oh, you know what?
- What?

18:53.312 --> 18:56.979
(Ben and Ashley chattering)

19:00.513 --> 19:02.780
- Attention, Camp Briarbrook!

19:02.780 --> 19:04.623
Before we continue with the debauchery,

19:04.623 --> 19:07.473
we have a very important
tradition to honor this evening.

19:09.093 --> 19:11.043
Now we all know the story.

19:11.043 --> 19:12.693
42 years ago, Nurse Agatha

19:12.693 --> 19:14.163
gets kicked out of Camp Briarbrook

19:14.163 --> 19:19.163
after her homeopathic remedies
get a little too witchy.

19:19.239 --> 19:20.796
- Ooh!

19:22.323 --> 19:24.003
- She resurfaces a few years later

19:24.003 --> 19:25.053
when a counselor finds her

19:25.053 --> 19:27.093
giving secret midnight medicine classes

19:27.093 --> 19:28.536
to campers in the woods.

19:30.543 --> 19:32.313
She's confronted.

19:32.313 --> 19:33.366
The kids go ape shit.

19:34.293 --> 19:36.933
Agatha takes off, trips,

19:36.933 --> 19:40.326
splits her head open
on a rock, bleeds out.

19:40.326 --> 19:43.323
(Peter moans)

19:43.323 --> 19:47.205
Ding dong, the bitch is dead.

19:47.205 --> 19:48.843
(Dylan laughs)

19:48.843 --> 19:50.103
- [Veronica] So gross.

19:50.103 --> 19:51.006
- Seconded.

19:52.533 --> 19:57.533
- But then this eerie calm
takes over the forest.

20:00.693 --> 20:05.693
All at once, the campers gather
around Agatha, grab hands,

20:06.723 --> 20:09.396
and begin to recite an
incantation until sunrise.

20:13.053 --> 20:15.073
Ex vitam immortalem.

20:19.646 --> 20:21.313
Ex vitam immortalem.

20:27.093 --> 20:28.713
Come on, say it with me!

20:28.713 --> 20:30.393
- [Group] Immortal life!

20:30.393 --> 20:31.506
- That's right!

20:32.430 --> 20:33.783
Now I know we've all been trying

20:33.783 --> 20:35.973
to bring this hag back for years,

20:35.973 --> 20:39.243
late nights in the bathroom,
the bunks, the woods,

20:39.243 --> 20:41.993
chanting for her like she
was Bloody Mary or something,

20:42.873 --> 20:47.256
but, guys, it's time to forget
the cute little limericks.

20:49.353 --> 20:51.783
If you'll please direct your
attention to Mondo Mike-

20:51.783 --> 20:53.144
- [Dylan] Boo, no one likes you, Mike.

20:53.144 --> 20:54.123
(Peter laughs)

20:54.123 --> 20:55.293
- [Peter] You'll notice
that he's distributing

20:55.293 --> 20:57.783
medical grade needles to each of you.

20:57.783 --> 21:01.293
You see, I've uncovered
the secret ingredient

21:01.293 --> 21:05.463
in our mission.
- Thank you.

21:05.463 --> 21:06.863
- We need to hurt ourselves.

21:08.073 --> 21:12.003
Not a lot, just enough so
that Agatha has something

21:12.003 --> 21:13.593
to come back and heal.

21:13.593 --> 21:15.153
- [Kellie] Really?

21:15.153 --> 21:17.013
- Yeah, no. I don't know.

21:17.013 --> 21:18.663
- It'll be fun. Trust me.

21:18.663 --> 21:20.038
- Yeah, but I mean, like-

21:20.038 --> 21:21.603
- Hey.

21:21.603 --> 21:23.886
It's not gonna hurt. I promise.

21:24.873 --> 21:26.973
- Now, on the count of
three, we prick our finger,

21:26.973 --> 21:28.983
hold it up to the sky,
and scream her name.

21:28.983 --> 21:30.873
- Peter, are these needles clean?

21:30.873 --> 21:33.663
I mean, as fun as this whole
blood brothers thing sounds,

21:33.663 --> 21:37.023
I'm not looking to end the
summer with some grodie disease.

21:37.023 --> 21:38.013
- Excellent question, Kellie.

21:38.013 --> 21:39.126
Yes!

21:40.023 --> 21:43.296
Yes. These needles are
sterile and ritual-ready.

21:44.343 --> 21:47.496
The question is, are you?

21:51.783 --> 21:52.616
- [Danny] I am.

21:57.633 --> 21:58.593
- Okay.

21:58.593 --> 21:59.543
- Thank you, Danny!

22:00.423 --> 22:02.436
That's the spirit Danny boy! Yes, sir!

22:06.243 --> 22:07.093
Then let's do it.

22:09.693 --> 22:12.213
Three, two, one.

22:15.264 --> 22:16.681
- [Group] Agatha!

22:21.538 --> 22:22.761
(Dylan screams)

22:22.761 --> 22:25.677
(group screams)

22:25.677 --> 22:26.873
(Dylan grunting)

22:26.873 --> 22:29.223
- Wow, Dylan. Real original.

22:29.223 --> 22:30.773
- It fucking worked, didn't it?

22:32.043 --> 22:32.876
Didn't it?!

22:36.393 --> 22:38.080
Fuck you all.

22:38.080 --> 22:42.586
Fucking idiots.

22:42.586 --> 22:44.466
- All right. Let's go to the beach.

22:46.074 --> 22:49.513
(engine putters)
- Come on.

22:49.513 --> 22:51.217
(engine putters)

22:51.217 --> 22:52.050
Come on!

22:53.763 --> 22:56.076
Come on, you son of a bitch! Pete!

22:58.668 --> 23:03.668
(kids chattering)
(ominous music)

23:06.123 --> 23:08.403
- Excuse me, Shawn. How much longer?

23:08.403 --> 23:09.893
I'm trying to calculate
when I should eat my snack

23:09.893 --> 23:11.983
so my blood sugar stays stable.

23:11.983 --> 23:15.358
(kids chattering)

23:15.358 --> 23:17.381
- I don't know, Dennis.

23:17.381 --> 23:20.692
(kids chattering)

23:20.692 --> 23:22.275
Hey, do me a favor?

23:23.393 --> 23:24.813
Do you think you can get your friends

23:24.813 --> 23:27.529
to play the quiet game
for like five minutes?

23:27.529 --> 23:29.433
(children chattering)

23:29.433 --> 23:32.173
- You and I both know
that's not gonna happen.

23:32.173 --> 23:33.653
(children chattering loudly)

23:33.653 --> 23:37.473
- [Kid 1] I'm also a bit afraid of sharks.

23:37.473 --> 23:39.657
Yeah, especially hammerhead sharks.

23:39.657 --> 23:41.701
- [Kid 2] Those are my
favorite kind of shark!

23:41.701 --> 23:45.201
(children yelling loudly)

23:52.829 --> 23:56.079
(children fall silent)

24:14.323 --> 24:15.843
- Good, yeah.

24:15.843 --> 24:16.676
All right.

24:19.173 --> 24:20.006
Quiet game.

24:23.553 --> 24:24.386
Good job, guys.

24:28.923 --> 24:29.756
All right.

24:47.523 --> 24:48.356
Fuck.

24:51.464 --> 24:53.051
(radiator hissing)

24:53.051 --> 24:55.634
(Shawn coughs)

25:04.083 --> 25:05.013
All right, guys.

25:05.013 --> 25:07.013
It looks like we're gonna be here for...

25:09.086 --> 25:11.753
(ominous music)

25:12.933 --> 25:14.406
What the fuck?

25:17.308 --> 25:19.023
(children chattering)

25:19.023 --> 25:20.652
- [Kid] He can see me.

25:20.652 --> 25:22.606
(ominous music)

25:22.606 --> 25:23.439
- Hey!

25:26.446 --> 25:27.279
Hey!

25:29.798 --> 25:30.631
Dennis!

25:32.941 --> 25:33.946
Tony!

25:33.946 --> 25:35.506
(children laughing)

25:35.506 --> 25:36.339
Martha!

25:37.624 --> 25:40.665
(ominous music)
(children chattering)

25:40.665 --> 25:42.347
- [Kid] Briarbrook.

25:42.347 --> 25:43.951
Briarbrook.
- Shit!

25:43.951 --> 25:45.951
- [Children] Briarbrook!

25:47.226 --> 25:49.449
- This is excruciating.

25:49.449 --> 25:51.183
- The shot clock's winding down.

25:51.183 --> 25:52.623
Please, make a move now.

25:52.623 --> 25:53.573
- What's happening?

25:54.723 --> 25:56.283
- Nothing.

25:56.283 --> 25:57.156
- Figures.

25:59.090 --> 26:01.043
♪ Tell me why you're all alone ♪

26:01.043 --> 26:03.963
(rock splashes)

26:03.963 --> 26:05.013
- [Danny] Can I help?

26:06.633 --> 26:07.466
- Sure.

26:09.993 --> 26:11.493
I should've known better than to practice

26:11.493 --> 26:12.873
where everyone could see me.

26:12.873 --> 26:14.703
- Yeah, I'm not gonna judge.

26:14.703 --> 26:16.074
I promise.

26:16.074 --> 26:17.283
- Well, I hope not, Danny.

26:17.283 --> 26:19.113
It's just skipping stones.

26:19.113 --> 26:20.763
- Okay, Kellie Parker.

26:20.763 --> 26:21.943
Do you want my help or not?

26:21.943 --> 26:26.196
- Well, Danny Patterson, I
think it was you who offered.

26:29.553 --> 26:31.503
- You're using the wrong rocks.

26:31.503 --> 26:32.336
- [Kellie] Oh?

26:34.323 --> 26:35.156
- May I?

26:36.303 --> 26:37.136
- [Kellie] Sure.

26:38.673 --> 26:40.443
- Um, okay.

26:40.443 --> 26:42.183
Well, there's this common misconception

26:42.183 --> 26:44.943
that your thumb is
supposed to go on the side,

26:44.943 --> 26:49.536
but it's actually supposed
to be on the top, like that.

26:50.763 --> 26:54.843
And then you move your
body in this position,

26:54.843 --> 26:56.676
and you angle, like that.

26:58.533 --> 27:03.533
And move your arm back, and release.

27:05.673 --> 27:06.744
Theoretically.

27:06.744 --> 27:08.763
(Kellie laughs)

27:08.763 --> 27:09.876
- A valiant effort.

27:14.733 --> 27:15.566
Danny?

27:16.503 --> 27:17.336
- Yeah?

27:18.513 --> 27:20.213
- Can I have my hand back, please?

27:21.406 --> 27:22.596
- Yeah, yeah, sure.

27:28.203 --> 27:29.036
- Um...

27:30.243 --> 27:31.076
- Shit.

27:32.163 --> 27:35.223
- Danny, uh, listen.

27:35.223 --> 27:37.623
I have this guy back at school.

27:37.623 --> 27:38.456
- No, you don't.

27:40.203 --> 27:41.133
- Excuse me?

27:41.133 --> 27:41.966
- I would've...

27:41.966 --> 27:43.120
Someone would have told me.

27:44.169 --> 27:45.272
- What?

27:45.272 --> 27:46.626
- Kellie, come on.

27:46.626 --> 27:47.486
- Come on, what?

27:47.486 --> 27:48.843
- Kellie, it doesn't have to be forever,

27:48.843 --> 27:49.676
just let me-

27:49.676 --> 27:50.509
- Let you?

27:50.509 --> 27:51.363
Jesus, Danny!
- Kellie, please.

27:51.363 --> 27:54.273
- You know what, going along
with this whole late night,

27:54.273 --> 27:56.283
let me show you how it's
done thing, that's on me.

27:56.283 --> 27:57.413
I'm sorry, but...

27:58.852 --> 28:01.435
(upbeat music)

28:11.520 --> 28:12.353
- Pay up.

28:13.398 --> 28:16.473
(Peter sighs)

28:16.473 --> 28:18.003
Thank you.

28:18.003 --> 28:18.843
- Finders keepers.

28:18.843 --> 28:20.073
- Hey! No.

28:20.073 --> 28:20.906
Give that back.

28:20.906 --> 28:21.739
- Come on, what's it worth to you?

28:21.739 --> 28:24.582
- You jackass!
- Come on, earn it!

28:24.582 --> 28:26.183
(Veronica bickering)

28:26.183 --> 28:27.154
(Dylan laughs)

28:27.154 --> 28:28.411
- [Veronica] Are you
fucking serious right now?

28:28.411 --> 28:29.553
Give it back to me.

28:29.553 --> 28:31.515
Dylan, what the actual fuck?
- Come on, you can get it.

28:31.515 --> 28:32.598
- No, stop!
- Aren't you fast?

28:32.598 --> 28:35.195
I thought you ran track?
- Stupid idiot.

28:35.195 --> 28:36.170
(indistinct)

28:36.170 --> 28:37.511
- No, I can't, I can't.

28:37.511 --> 28:38.344
I can't.

28:41.486 --> 28:43.173
- Are you okay?

28:43.173 --> 28:44.133
- Yeah, yeah.

28:44.133 --> 28:48.873
It's just, there's this
guy back at Dartmouth.

28:48.873 --> 28:50.886
It's not totally official.

28:52.113 --> 28:54.813
- Oh. I don't think you've
mentioned him before.

28:54.813 --> 28:57.093
- No, no, I just,

28:57.093 --> 28:58.863
he's been writing me letters all summer

28:58.863 --> 29:00.513
telling me how rad he thinks I am,

29:00.513 --> 29:02.063
and I've written a couple back.

29:04.983 --> 29:06.363
- Do you like him?

29:06.363 --> 29:07.323
- Who, Danny?

29:07.323 --> 29:08.156
Or...

29:09.093 --> 29:10.569
- Either.

29:10.569 --> 29:14.071
- Uh, I don't know.

29:14.071 --> 29:18.536
The Dartmouth guy, uh,
he's there, you know?

29:18.536 --> 29:19.469
- [Danny] Kellie.

29:19.469 --> 29:20.486
- Oh, Danny, I-

29:20.486 --> 29:21.579
(rock thuds)

29:21.579 --> 29:22.412
- [Peter] Shit!

29:22.412 --> 29:23.375
(rock thudding)
(Danny grunting)

29:23.375 --> 29:24.208
- Back up!
- Danny!

29:24.208 --> 29:25.166
- Back up!
(Lauren screams)

29:25.166 --> 29:26.426
- [Lauren] Danny, what the fuck!

29:26.426 --> 29:28.453
- Jeez!
(Lauren screams)

29:28.453 --> 29:29.856
- Danny, what the fuck?!

29:29.856 --> 29:30.814
Danny!

29:30.814 --> 29:32.443
- Peter!

29:32.443 --> 29:33.651
Peter!

29:33.651 --> 29:35.368
- Fucking psycho!

29:35.368 --> 29:37.932
(ominous music)

29:37.932 --> 29:38.765
- [Mike] Back up!

29:38.765 --> 29:40.180
Back up!

29:40.180 --> 29:42.152
(Danny screams)

29:42.152 --> 29:44.819
(ominous music)

29:52.337 --> 29:55.254
(Veronica panting)

29:57.703 --> 30:00.870
(Danny cries in pain)

30:02.269 --> 30:04.936
(ominous music)

30:12.156 --> 30:14.823
(Danny screams)

30:21.628 --> 30:23.788
(Danny screams)

30:23.788 --> 30:26.455
(ominous music)

30:33.969 --> 30:34.802
- Mike?

30:38.432 --> 30:39.265
Mike?

30:41.612 --> 30:42.963
- We gotta...

30:42.963 --> 30:44.930
We gotta get to the mess hall.

30:44.930 --> 30:47.403
We gotta call the cops, okay?

30:47.403 --> 30:50.070
We gotta call the cops.
(Veronica hyperventilates)

30:50.070 --> 30:52.443
- Hey, it's okay. Look at me.
- Yeah? It's okay, Lauren?

30:52.443 --> 30:53.276
This is okay to you?

30:53.276 --> 30:55.693
- All right, everybody
just calm the fuck down.

30:55.693 --> 30:56.526
- [Lauren] It's okay, it's okay.

30:56.526 --> 30:57.366
- This just happened.

30:58.323 --> 30:59.403
I don't know why, but it did,

30:59.403 --> 31:01.143
and the longer we wait to do something,

31:01.143 --> 31:02.043
the worse it's gonna get.

31:02.043 --> 31:03.123
- Yeah, Mike, it's gonna get worse.

31:03.123 --> 31:04.173
It's gonna get worse than this?!

31:04.173 --> 31:05.973
- Dylan, I swear to fucking God,

31:05.973 --> 31:07.023
now's not the time!

31:07.023 --> 31:08.493
- What? Are you fucking kidding me, man?

31:08.493 --> 31:09.429
You just stabbed a guy!

31:09.429 --> 31:10.262
- She's dead!

31:10.262 --> 31:11.643
- [Dylan] You're gonna
stab more fucking people?!

31:11.643 --> 31:12.476
- Fuck you!

31:14.220 --> 31:18.803
(counselors chattering simultaneously)

31:20.043 --> 31:21.543
- One at a time!

31:21.543 --> 31:23.193
- Something happened
at the lake with Danny.

31:23.193 --> 31:24.026
- Is he hurt?

31:24.026 --> 31:26.796
- He killed Kellie, and I killed him.

31:28.023 --> 31:28.856
- What?

31:28.856 --> 31:30.333
- Dude just fucking snapped.

31:30.333 --> 31:31.503
- Danny wouldn't do that.

31:31.503 --> 31:32.793
- Yeah?

31:32.793 --> 31:34.326
Well, he fucking did.

31:36.771 --> 31:39.438
(ominous music)

31:44.413 --> 31:47.523
- I'm gonna call the police.

31:47.523 --> 31:49.461
- [Veronica] I wanna go now.
- [Lauren] It's gonna be okay.

31:49.461 --> 31:52.103
- Hey, we're gonna figure
this out, all right?

31:52.103 --> 31:52.936
It's gonna be okay.

31:52.936 --> 31:54.693
- Ben and Ashley, they
weren't at the beach.

31:54.693 --> 31:56.013
They went (indistinct) remember?

31:56.013 --> 31:56.846
- [Mike] She's right.

31:56.846 --> 31:58.233
- What?
- They're still down there.

31:58.233 --> 31:59.066
- Oh, shit!

31:59.066 --> 31:59.899
- Yes...

31:59.899 --> 32:03.091
(telephone explodes)
(Heather screams)

32:03.091 --> 32:04.627
- Oh! Damn it!

32:04.627 --> 32:06.486
- Oh, shit!

32:06.486 --> 32:08.283
What the hell? We need to find someone.

32:08.283 --> 32:09.483
- Your grandfather took the truck.

32:09.483 --> 32:11.083
He's not due back 'til tomorrow.

32:11.973 --> 32:13.743
- Guys, what are we supposed to do?

32:13.743 --> 32:15.963
- Shawn, he's coming back in an hour.

32:15.963 --> 32:16.923
- I'll go to the infirmary.

32:16.923 --> 32:17.943
I'll get something to help.

32:17.943 --> 32:20.403
- I have gauze, just find antiseptic.

